	(1,1,'2016-04-20 20:39:00','2016-04-21 00:39:00','Winthrop-University Hospital acquired Women’s Oncology Associates, a medical practice that has been serving the community of Garden City, Long Island for over 30 years.\r\n\r\nWhether you have gynecologic, breast or colorectal cancer, our approach at Women’s Oncology Associates is simple – we believe that cancer is not the only part of you that needs care. We understand that you are dynamic and we have established a full array of services to help you and your family continue to live your lives while you undergo treatment.\r\n\r\nThis includes integrative therapies that help ease the discomfort, nutritionists to make sure you’re taking in enough of the right kinds of foods to keep you strong, navigators to help guide you through the maze of appointments, a friendly dog to pet while you get chemo, and support groups to share your thoughts with other women who understand.','Women\'s Oncology Associates Is Now A Winthrop Medical Affiliate','Winthrop-University Hospital acquired Women’s Oncology Associates, a medical practice that has been serving the community of Garden City, Long Island for over 30 years. ','publish','closed','closed','','womens-oncology-associates-is-now-a-winthrop-medical-affiliate','','','2016-04-26 15:17:29','2016-04-26 19:17:29','',0,'https://$HTTP_HOST/?p=1',0,'post','',0),
